               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-255-person2221">
                  JAMES 
                  TAYLOR
               <interp inst="t18300415-255-person2221" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-255-person2221" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-255-person2221" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a butcher, and live in the Cityroad. On the 26th of March I saw the two prisoners together, in Bath-street, not ten minutes walk from the prosecutor's - Wiltshire had an apron, and when I got close to them, I saw the spout of this tea-kettle; I passed them and saw them turn up a court - I went round Old-street, and saw them again; Cooke had then got the apron on, and the kettle open in his hand - I told the officer; I ran and took Cooke and Barrows took Wiltshire - I found these boots on Cooke, and a duplicate of an article pawned the same day.</p>
               <p>
            
