                  </persName>
            . I was serjeant of the Police. The prisoners were brought in, and charged with stealing this tea-kettle; when I was taking them to Worship-street, I heard Cooke ask Wiltshire what he should say - he said he did not know: Cooke said, "Say we found it" - Wiltshire said No; Cooke then said, "Say it was given you to carry:" and that was the defence they made before the Magistrate.</p>
